Judul: Printed Playbooks, Performance, and the 1580s Lag
Abstrak: The article offers information on the printed publication of drama of 1580s in England, discussing their performances. Topics discussed include the book "Seneca His Tenne Tragedies" written by translator Thomas Newton; the theater industry of London, England during the 1580s and 1590s; and the play "Three Ladies of London" written by Robert Wilson.
